  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large pot (big enough to fit all your ingredients inside and with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced red onion</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> of <strong>sugar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-5 min or until softened but not coloured</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-one-pot-puttanesca/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Slice the<strong> black olives </strong>finely</p><p>Grate the <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-one-pot-puttanesca/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 500ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> to the softened onions and stir in the <strong>veg stock mix</strong></p><p>Increase the heat to high and bring to the boil</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-one-pot-puttanesca/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the stock is boiling, reduce the heat to medium and add the<strong> linguine</strong> (you can break it in half if it doesn't fit)</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>capers</strong>, <strong>sliced olives</strong> and<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Tip: Push the pasta into the liquid fully, so it cooks!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-one-pot-puttanesca/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous amount of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for 5-8 min or until the linguine is cooked</p><p>Tip: Keep checking that the linguine has not stuck to the base of the pot and stir if needed</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-one-pot-puttanesca/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the linguine is cooked, remove the lid and stir continuously for 3-5 min or until a sauce forms, adding more water if it looks too dry</p><p>Tip: Stirring the sauce releases the starch from the pasta making it naturally creamier</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-one-pot-puttanesca/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>chives</strong> finely</p><p>Once done, remove the cooked <strong>linguine</strong> and sauce from the heat and stir in <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped chives</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save some for garnish!) – this is your <strong>puttanesca</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-one-pot-puttanesca/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>puttanesca </strong>with the <strong>rocket</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped chives</strong>, <strong>remaining Italian hard cheese </strong>and a good grind of<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
